description._content: Original Collection: E. E. Wilson Photographic Collection (P 101) Item Number: P101:0443b Image Description: The Corvallis Carriage and Wagon Co. factory (later Coast Carriage and Wagon Factory) was located between 11th and 13th Streets next to the Oregon and Pacific railroad. The building was constructed in 1892, but by 1896 the factory had failed. The building was later used by the Corvallis Feed and Seed Company.
